#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:1
msgid "_validate_weights"
msgstr "_validate_weights"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:3
msgid "Firma"
msgstr "Signature"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:12
msgid "Che problema risolve"
msgstr "What problem it solves"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:14
msgid "Centralizza la validazione dei pesi usati nelle statistiche pesate."
msgstr "Centralizes validation of the weights used in weighted statistics."

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:16
msgid "Contratto sugli input"
msgstr "Input contract"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:18
msgid "Se `w is None`, restituisce `None` e il chiamante ricade nel caso non pesato."
msgstr "If `w is None`, it returns `None` and the caller falls back to the unweighted case."

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:19
msgid "Se `w` e presente, viene prima convertito con [`_as_float_vector`](as-float-vector.md)."
msgstr "If `w` is provided, it is first converted with [`_as_float_vector`](as-float-vector.md)."

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:20
msgid "`w` deve avere la stessa forma di `x`."
msgstr "`w` must have the same shape as `x`."

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:21
msgid "Ogni peso deve essere strettamente positivo."
msgstr "Each weight must be strictly positive."

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:22
msgid "Anche la somma dei pesi deve essere strettamente positiva e finita."
msgstr "The sum of the weights must also be strictly positive and finite."

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:24
msgid "Dove viene usata"
msgstr "Where it is used"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:26
msgid "[`weighted_mean`](../../moduli/stats_utils/weighted-mean.md)"
msgstr "[`weighted_mean`](../../moduli/stats_utils/weighted-mean.md)"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:27
msgid "[`variance`](../../moduli/stats_utils/variance.md)"
msgstr "[`variance`](../../moduli/stats_utils/variance.md)"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:28
msgid "[`covariance`](../../moduli/stats_utils/covariance.md)"
msgstr "[`covariance`](../../moduli/stats_utils/covariance.md)"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:30
msgid "Come fallisce"
msgstr "Failure modes"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:32
msgid "`ValueError` se `w` non ha la stessa forma di `x`"
msgstr "`ValueError` if `w` does not have the same shape as `x`"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:33
msgid "`ValueError` se contiene zeri, valori negativi, `NaN` o infiniti"
msgstr "`ValueError` if it contains zeros, negative values, `NaN` values, or infinities"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:34
msgid "`ValueError` se la somma dei pesi non e positiva"
msgstr "`ValueError` if the sum of the weights is not positive"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:36
msgid "Perche resta privata"
msgstr "Why it stays private"

#: ../../source/checks/stats_utils/validate-weights.md:38
msgid ""
"Serve a imporre una convenzione comune sui pesi senza introdurre una funzione aggiuntiva nell'API"
" pubblica."
msgstr ""
"It enforces a shared convention for weights without introducing an extra function into the public"
" API."

